\begin_layout Standard
\align center

\size larger
Abstract
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Portfolio optimization is one of the best-known and most widely used methods
 in financial portfolio selection.
 The classical mean-variance portfolio selection model of Markowitz, H.
 has been widely recognized as one of the cornerstones of modern portfolio
 theory.
 However, the analytical results indicate that a mean-variance efficient
 portfolio's weights can be extremely sensitive from error of input parameters;
 expected return and risk.
 Recently, a robust optimization model is proposed for concurring this issue,
 which considers uncertainty of input parameters.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This paper examines the effectiveness of the robust optimization portfolio
 through comparing the rolling-window performances between mean-variance
 portfolio and robust optimization portfolio, by forecasting the several
 expected returns of multiple bond and equity indices.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The first experiments evaluate the historical performance of portfolio.
 The portfolio is built with expected return, risks, and uncertainty in
 expected returns were generated by vector autoregressive; VAR process.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The second experiments evaluate the historical performance of portfolio,
 which is the non-conditional and conditional expectation in VAR model with
 its estimation error.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The third experiments evaluate the historical performance of portfolio which
 is the non-conditional and conditional expectation in autoregressive; AR
 model with its estimation error.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These results indicate that estimation error of expected return gives less
 affect on robust optimization portfolio weights.
 Furthermore, robust optimization portfolio is useful for stable portfolio
 construction because it avoid the loss of downside risks.
 Moreover, these result shows that it is effective for robust optimization
 portfolio to give a non-conditional expectation with adequate uncertainty
 set.
\end_layout

